<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 1:39PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Elevated Fire Weather Conditions This Afternoon...
A combination of dry and breezy conditions will continue an
enhanced risk for the active spread of wildfires this afternoon.
West to northwest winds of 10 to 20 mph, with gusts 25 to 35 mph
can be expected to continue through late afternoon. Relative
humidity has dropped to 15 to 25 percent. This has resulted in
elevated fire weather conditions that would support rapid rates of
spread for wildland fires.
Please refer to your local burn permitting authorities on whether
you can burn. If you do burn, use extreme caution since fires can
quickly get out of hand under these conditions.</description>
